{{UpgradeTask426}} ensures that all users have a {{display_name}} and {{last_name}} during the upgrade to Crowd 2.1. However, the implementation assumes that the number of users to modify is small. When it's large, the upgrade task will run extremely slowly and may fail. The log will show:

{noformat}
Running upgrade task for build - 426: Updating users in internal directories to have non-empty display names and last names
{noformat}

as the last line.

To avoid various confusing situations with SSL bugs in various SSL implementations it's very convenient to be able to force a specific SSL version on the client side.  

For example https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-24035 suggests providing such a solution to force SSL v3.  Or searching for solutions to a bad_record_mac error will find various products telling you what system property can be used to force SSL v3.

It seems likely that such a system property in Crowd's LDAP support too.  E.g. 
{noformat}
-Dcrowd.ldap.forcesslv3=true
{noformat}

Currently, user will be able to create group name with trailing empty space as a result Crowd and external integrate product will treat trailing empty space as part of the group name for example:
{code}
bamboo-admin<empty space> 
{code}
and 
{code}
bamboo-admin
{code}
Both above group will be treated differently and some external application will throw an error notifying that the default require groups does not exist

As mentioned on Crowd Apple Open Directory connector configuration documentation [here|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CROWD/Apple+Open+Directory#AppleOpenDirectory-GroupRelationships]:

{quote}
*Group Relationships*

Crowd will check both the gidNumber and the memberUid attributes to determine if a user is a member of a group. The name of the gidNumber attribute is not configurable — Crowd will always use this attribute to determine membership.

The [RFC 2307 schema|http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2307.txt] does not support nesting of groups, so Crowd does not support nested groups in Apple Open Directory.{quote}

Crowd currently does not support nested group for this connector configuration.

